  <note line="3" original="kāya nottha (syā. ka.)" reference-line="8" id="0">
    <alternatives>
      <alternative lang="vri">kāya nuttha</alternative>
      <alternative lang="syā. ka.">kāya nottha</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <previous>Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane. Poṭṭhapādopi kho paribbājako aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho poṭṭhapādaṃ paribbājakaṃ bhagavā etadavoca – kāya nuttha </previous>
  </note>
  <note line="11" original="na kho nāmetaṃ (sī. pī.)" reference-line="11" id="1">
    <alternatives>
      <alternative lang="vri">pana metaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative lang="sī. pī.">na kho nāmetaṃ</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <previous>Tamañño evamāha – ‘na kho pana metaṃ </previous>
  </note>
  <note line="19" original="purimasaññā (ka.)" reference-line="21" id="2">
    <alternatives>
      <alternative lang="vri">rūpasaññā</alternative>
      <alternative lang="ka.">purimasaññā</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <previous> ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. Tassa yā purimā rūpasaññā </previous>
  </note>
  <note line="27" original="kabaḷīkārabhakkhanti (syā. ka.)" reference-line="29" id="3">
