    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <previous> yathā aññāva saññā bhavissati añño attā. Tiṭṭhateva sāyaṃ </previous>
  </note>
  <note line="43" original="evaṃ (ka.)" reference-line="32" id="5">
    <alternatives>
      <alternative lang="vri">etaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative lang="ka.">evaṃ</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <previous> Sakkā panetaṃ, bhante, mayā ñātuṃ – ‘saññā purisassa attā’ti vā ‘aññāva saññā añño attāti vā’ti? Dujjānaṃ kho etaṃ </previous>
  </note>
  <note line="51" original="vācāya (syā. ka.)" reference-line="39" id="6">
    <alternatives>
      <alternative lang="vri">vācā</alternative>
      <alternative lang="syā. ka.">vācāya</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <previous> kho te paribbājakā acirapakkantassa bhagavato poṭṭhapādaṃ paribbājakaṃ samantato vācā </previous>
  </note>
  <note line="59" original="kañci (pī.)" reference-line="39" id="7">
    <alternatives>
      <alternative lang="vri">kiñci</alternative>
      <alternative lang="pī.">kañci</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <previous> sannitodakena sañjhabbharimakaṃsu – evameva panāyaṃ bhavaṃ poṭṭhapādo yaññadeva samaṇo gotamo bhāsati, taṃ tadevassa abbhanumodati – ‘evametaṃ bhagavā evametaṃ, sugatā’ti. Na kho pana mayaṃ kiñci </previous>
  </note>
